title: Did the White House give Leslie Stahl an empty book on Trump's achievements in health care?
subtitle: "A perfect metaphor for Trump's presidency," alleged by critics. What really happened?
author: Dan MacGuill
vclaim: In October 2020, the press secretary gave the White House Kaylie McKinney "60 Minutes" to Leslie Stahl's reporter a large book of achievements of United States President Donald Trump in health care, which was empty.
